  "texts": [
    "The upper flux limit data will be available in two ways: either by downloading the pre-computed data products or through a web tool.",
    "Half-sky mapsHalf-sky counts, count rate and exposure maps are offered (in HiPS format) in seven different energy bands:-0.2-2.3 keV (Main) -0.2-0.6 keV -0.6-2.3 keV -2.3-5.0 keV (Hard) -0.2-0.5 keV -0.5-1.0 keV -1.0-2.0 keV, while the background maps and the sensitivity maps based on aperture photometry are released only for the first four energy bands above.",
    "As an example, Fig. 15 shows the half-sky images in Zenith Equal Area projection colour coded by count rate intensity in four bands: 0.2-0.6 keV, 0.6-2.3 keV, 2.3-5 keV and 0.2-2.3 keV, respectively.",
    "These images have been created using all TMs (also those affected by light leak), so some artifacts are still present in the lowest-energy map.",
    "On the other hand, at the highest energy (2.3-5 keV) the count rate maps are dominated by the (unvignetted) particle background; small temporal fluctuations of such background (including rare Coronal Mass Ejections hitting SRG) are imprinted on those maps as stripes at fixed ecliptic longitudesfoot_11."
